docs.lead_paragraph: TOKYO — Carlos Ghosn, who created an alliance between Nissan and Renault that made it effectively the world’s largest carmaker, was arrested by the authorities in Japan on Monday in a remarkable tumble for one of the industry’s most powerful and admired leaders.

headline.main: Nissan Chairman, Carlos Ghosn, Is Arrested Over Financial Misconduct Allegations

docs.abstract: The internet giant is expanding an identification program ahead of the European Parliament vote in May.

docs.lead_paragraph: LONDON — Google said on Wednesday that it would begin requiring more information from buyers of online ads linked to next year’s European Parliament elections, expanding a program introduced for political ads in the United States.
